description: Consider the Diophantine equation x^3 + y^3 = z^3 + 1 (1<x<y<z) or 'Fermat near misses'. Arrange solutions by increasing values of z (see A050791), and increasing values of y in case of ties. Sequence gives values of y.
comments: Values of y associated with A050794.
references: Ian Stewart, "Game, Set and Math", Chapter 8, 'Close Encounters of the Fermat Kind', Penguin Books, Ed. 1991, pp. 107-124.
David Wells, "Curious and Interesting Numbers", Revised Ed. 1997, Penguin Books, On number "729", p. 147.
links: Lewis Mammel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..368
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Diophantine Equation - 3rd Powers
example: For the 10th term where y is 2304, 577^3 + 2304^3 = 2316^3 + 1.
author: _Patrick De Geest_, Sep 15 1999
extensions: More terms from Michel ten Voorde (seqfan(AT)tenvoorde.org); no more with z<8192.
More terms from Don Reble (djr(AT)nk.ca), Nov 29 2001
Edited by _N. J. A. Sloane_, May 08 2007
